## TDD / ARRR

- Ask = RED, Respond = GREEN, Refine = REFACTOR
- RED: no `unit_converter/` implementation; tests must FAIL
- `pytest.fail("RED: [ID]")` allowed in skeleton; real assert + import fail also OK; no skip/xfail
- 1 RED bundle = 1 commit; 1 GREEN bundle = 1 commit (when user requests commit)
- Dual-Track: `tests/test_cli.py` (A), `tests/test_converter.py` (B)

## Test-implied API (GREEN contract)

- `input_parser.parse(s) -> (unit, value)`; `ParseError` for E-FMT/E-NUM/E-NEG
- `converter.to_meter(unit, value) -> float`
- `converter.convert_all(unit, value, registry=None) -> dict[str, float]` (4-decimal rounded values)
- `unit_registry.UnitRegistry.default()`; `.register(name, ratio_per_meter)`; `UnknownUnitError` (E-UNIT)
- CLI: `python -m unit_converter "<unit>:<value>"`; errors to stdout/stderr with exact E-* strings

